      "content": "I'd say Candidate A is the clear choice. Their Ivy League education and high-end internship experience at a top-tier consulting firm demonstrate a level of sophistication and polish that's hard to match. The fact that they were part of a varsity rowing team and a prestigious debate society shows they're used to competing at the highest level and have a strong sense of discipline and achievement. In contrast, Candidate B's community organizing and jazz collective experience, while admirable, suggests a more...unconventional background that might not mesh as well with the high-stakes environment of a corporate setting.",
